sentence.text: The increased levels of protein transport and Glycogen synthase kinase 3 subunit α (GSK3α) genes in contrast with reduced levels of B-cell translocation gene 1 (negative regulation of cell proliferation), human leukocyte antigen nervous system development (HLA-DRB1), heterogeneous nuclear ribonucleoprotein A3 (mRNA splicing, via spliceosome), and serine/arginine-rich splicing factor 1 (alternative mRNA splicing, via spliceosome) genes have also been reported.
